--------------------
 SMURF FILE MANAGER
--------------------

    This is a file manager program that runs on text mode only.

    The program displays a list of directory contents in the screen and
    you should move through these list using your keyboard arrows.
    
    Actions like copy, delete, move, ... are taken when you press some
    special keys, defined bellow.
    

------------
 NAVIGATION
------------

    ArrowUp, ArrowDown, PageUp, PageDown
                    
                    move though the list of contents

    ArrowLeft, ArrowRight
                    
                    change current directory


--------------
 SPECIAL KEYS
--------------

    q   quit

    h   go to home directory

    g   you will be prompted for a directory to go
    
    x   select (or unselect) item under cursor and move bellow
    
    X   select (or unselect) item under cursor and move above
    
    a   select (or unselect) all items

    ;   call some program to open the file under cursor, or previously
        selected files

    :   execute command on the item under cursor or previously selected 
        items. If your command starts with "!" the command will be
        considered a system command, and will be executed in the current
        directory.
    
    d   delete item under cursor or selected items
    
    c   copy item under cursor or selected items
    
    m   move item under cursor or selected items
    
    r   refresh the screen (read directory contents again)
    
    o   set file information options, can be any combination of [altr]
            a - list hidden files
            l - display detailed file information
            t - order the list by last modified time 
            r - reverse the list order

    /   you will be prompted for a regular expression
        only files that match your regular expression will be shown

    n   create new directory


